Efficiency: teams get things done more efficiently than lone individuals.
Pooling skills: a good team will let everyone use their individual skills to the full.
Social: working together is fun for social animals like humans.
Learning: we can learn from other members of the team.
Leadership: teamwork is a context for leadership skills to shine.
Following: followership is just as important as leadership; teamwork helps us to develop this skill.
Problem solving: good teamwork teaches us to resolve problems effectively.
